\begin_layout Standard
The term SCADA, in automation, refers to monitoring, control and data acquisitio
n systems composed of one or more computers, monitoring and controlling
 a process.
 It will be presented a supervisory control and data acquisition system
 for equipment used in laboratories of control and automation of the School
 of Technology (EST), allowing remote control of them, increasing the safety
 of users.
 To do this, the physical processes were chosen, who are in the labs to
 simulate and implement the SCADA system, thus creating the interface for
 remote access thereof, improving the learning of students it can compare
 theory with practice, without risks of them, and at any time.
\end_layout

